. Docker Hub Access Token (For Jenkins)
For Jenkins to push your built Java image to Docker Hub, you need a Docker Hub token. Do not use your actual account password in Jenkins; use an access token instead.

Steps to generate:

Log in to Docker Hub in your browser.

Click your profile picture in the top right and select Account settings.

Go to the Security tab on the left menu.

Click New Access Token.

Give it a description (e.g., "Jenkins Pipeline").

Set Access permissions to Read & Write.

Click Generate.

Copy this token. In Jenkins, go to Manage Jenkins > Credentials > System > Global credentials > Add Credentials. Select "Username with password", enter your Docker Hub username, and paste this token as the password. Name the ID dockerhub-creds.
